comments.body:
This is not a bug.  We decided that when going from 3.0 to 3.1, you *must* install the enterprise plugins (Netapp and VMware), so these modules are required by the script.  If you run:

{noformat}
yum groupinstall eucalyptus-cloud-controller --nogpgcheck
{noformat}

that will install the necessary packages for the upgrade to succeed.  

I originally misread this issue summary as "2.0.3" rather than "3.0.2", and I do expect that there may be a problem with upgrades from 2.0.3 due to this new code, but we'll deal with that in a separate issue.
